### Temporal Analysis (pure Python math)

#### [NEW] [temporal.py](file:///c:/Users/baisa/Desktop/pulse-ai/agents/insight/temporal.py)

Four functions, all pure pandas/Python:

| Function | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `compare_windows` | Split data into two trailing windows (recent vs prior), compute per-region aggregate, return pct_change sorted ascending |
| `detect_outlier_regions` | Regions whose `abs(pct_change)` exceeds `2 × noise_pct` |
| `cluster_complaint_segment` | From support tickets for a given region in last N days, return dominant complaint category and its share |
| `correlate_in_time` | Score 0–1 based on temporal proximity of competitor event to decline start |

**Window design**: `compare_windows` takes `window_a_days=15, window_b_days=15` as defaults. Window A = last 15 days of data. Window B = the 15 days before that. This splits the 30-day CSV cleanly in half and captures the accelerating decline in the outlier.

